<!-- Speaker Notes:
Welcome. This session covers every high-yield trauma topic on the Surgery Shelf in one sitting. Trauma accounts for 20-25% of the exam — roughly 25 of 110 questions. We'll cover 10 domains with MCQs after each section. One principle unifies everything: stabilize before you scan. If a question offers CT for an unstable patient, that's always wrong. Let's begin.

> Shelf Tip: Trauma questions are spread across NBME organ systems. There's no standalone "trauma" category — recognize patterns in any system block.
